content:
This code snippet is part of optimizing font rendering quality in Panda3D by adjusting the pixel density for better clarity, particularly useful when dealing with larger text sizes. It demonstrates how to set a higher pixel-per-unit value than the default setting to reduce blurring and enhance sharpness. This adjustment is crucial for improving text readability in applications where font quality is paramount.

**Context:** The chunk appears within the "Font Quality" section of the document, illustrating methods to enhance text rendering clarity by modifying pixel density settings. It showcases both Python and C++ implementations for adjusting pixels per unit to address potential blurring issues with larger characters.

python

font.setPixelsPerUnit(60)

cpp

PT(TextFont) font=FontPool::load_font("arial.ttf");
PT(DynamicTextFont) dfont = DCAST(DynamicTextFont, font);
dfont->set_pixels_per_unit(60);
